### Proposed 5-group consolidation (pending approval)

If the portal must show exactly 5 categories, merge the 8 into 5 thematic groups:

| # | Consolidated category | Merged from |
|---|----------------------|-------------|
| 1 | Health & Wellness | Health, Nutrition & Wellness |
| 2 | Education, Skill & Youth | Education, Skill & Youth |
| 3 | Women & Child Development | Women Empowerment & Livelihood + Child Development |
| 4 | Governance & Community Welfare | Governance & Service Delivery + Social Welfare & Community |
| 5 | Development, Culture & Startups | Agriculture, Development & Environment + Tourism, Culture & Startups |

Implementation note: support consolidation without losing the original grouping by giving `categories` an optional self-relationship (`parent`) or a `group` select field, so the 8 detailed categories can roll up into 5 display groups.

## 4. Content Model (Payload CMS)

Existing template collections: `pages`, `posts`, `media`, `categories`, `users`; globals `header`, `footer` (see `src/payload.config.ts`). Reuse them and add a dedicated `yojnas` collection.

```mermaid
graph TD
  Cat["categories (8 seeded, CMS-managed)"] -->|relationship hasMany| Yoj["yojnas (scheme catalog)"]
  Yoj -->|upload| Media["media"]
  Yoj -->|optional relatedNews| Posts["posts (news/updates)"]
  Cat -->|optional| Posts
  Pages["pages (Layout Builder)"] -->|blocks| Home["Home + landing pages"]
  Cat -.->|optional parent rollup| Cat
```

### `yojnas` (new collection)
Scheme catalog. Mirror the `posts` collection conventions (draft/publish via `versions.drafts`, `slugField`, SEO tab, `populatePublishedAt`, `revalidate` hooks) for consistency.

Fields:
- `title` (text, required) - scheme name.
- `slug` (slugField) - URL.
- `category` (relationship -> `categories`, hasMany: false or true if a scheme spans categories; required).
- `summary` (textarea) - one-line description for cards and meta.
- `heroImage` (upload -> `media`).
- `content` (richText / lexical) - full description.
- `department` (text) - owning Raipur department.
- `beneficiaries` (textarea) - who it is for.
- `eligibility` (richText or textarea).
- `benefits` (richText or textarea).
- `howToApply` (richText) - steps; may link out.
- `status` (select: `active` | `upcoming` | `closed`; default `active`).
- `launchDate` (date, optional).
- `externalLink` (text/url, optional) - official application/source page.
- `relatedNews` (relationship -> `posts`, hasMany, optional).
- SEO fields via the SEO plugin (meta tab), like `posts`.

Admin: `useAsTitle: 'title'`; default columns `title`, `category`, `status`, `updatedAt`; access read = `anyone`, write = `authenticated` (match template `access/` helpers).

### `categories` (extend existing)
Currently `title` + `slug` only (`src/collections/Categories.ts`). Extend with:
- `description` (textarea, optional) - shown on category landing.
- `icon` or `color` (text/select, optional) - for category color-coding in UI.
- `group` (select, optional) OR `parent` (relationship -> `categories`, optional) - to support the 5-group rollup in section 3.

### `posts` (reuse as-is)
News, announcements, and updates. Optionally relate to a `category` and to `yojnas` via `relatedNews`.

### `pages` (reuse as-is)
Home and static/landing pages via the Layout Builder blocks.

### Seeding
Extend the existing seed flow (`src/app/(frontend)/next/seed/route.ts` and `src/endpoints/seed/`) to create the 8 categories and a representative set of yojnas from `ProjectCtg.xlsx`.

## 5. Site Map & Page Responsibilities

```mermaid
graph TD
  Home["/ Home"] --> Yojnas["/yojnas listing + filter + search"]
  Home --> CatLand["/categories/[slug] category landing"]
  Yojnas --> YojDetail["/yojnas/[slug] scheme detail"]
  CatLand --> YojDetail
  Home --> News["/posts news feed (existing)"]
  News --> PostDetail["/posts/[slug] (existing)"]
  Home --> Search["/search (existing)"]
```

- `/` Home (Pages + Layout Builder): hero/mission banner, the category grid (8 or 5), featured/active yojnas, latest news, search entry.
- `/yojnas` Listing: card grid of all yojnas with category filter, status filter, and search; paginated like `/posts`.
- `/yojnas/[slug]` Detail: hero, summary, department/beneficiaries/eligibility/benefits/how-to-apply, status badge, external link, related news.
- `/categories/[slug]` Category landing: category description + its yojnas.
- `/posts`, `/posts/[slug]`, `/search`: reuse existing template routes for news and search.

Header/Footer globals updated with Yojna Portal nav: Home, Yojnas, Categories, News, Search.

## 6. Design System, Accessibility & i18n

- **Aesthetic:** trustworthy government portal - clean, high-contrast, restrained. A measured tri-color-inspired accent palette (saffron/green accents on a neutral base), not loud. Per-category color-coding for wayfinding.
- **Layout:** card-based catalog, prominent search + filters, generous spacing, clear hierarchy. Mobile-first.
- **Components:** build on the template's existing shadcn/ui + TailwindCSS; reuse `Card`, `Media`, pagination, and rich-text rendering.
- **Accessibility:** WCAG 2.1 AA - semantic landmarks, keyboard navigable filters, visible focus states, alt text on all media, color contrast >= 4.5:1, status conveyed by text + color (not color alone).
- **i18n readiness:** model and UI should not hardcode English-only strings; plan for Hindi/English (scope TBD in section 8). Use Unicode-safe slugs.
- **Performance:** static generation + on-demand revalidation (existing template caching strategy); optimized `media` images.

## 7. Implementation Phases

1. **Data model:** add `yojnas` collection; extend `categories`; register `yojnas` in `src/payload.config.ts`; regenerate `payload-types.ts`.
2. **Seed:** populate 8 categories + sample yojnas from `ProjectCtg.xlsx`.
3. **Routes/UI:** build `/yojnas`, `/yojnas/[slug]`, `/categories/[slug]`; home category grid + featured/news sections; update Header/Footer nav.
4. **Search & filters:** wire yojnas into the search plugin; add category/status filters.
5. **Design polish:** category color-coding, status badges, accessibility pass, responsive QA.
6. **i18n:** (conditional) add Hindi/English fields or localization once scope is confirmed.

## 8. Open Decisions

- **Categories 8 vs 5:** Excel defines 8; brief said 5. Default is to seed all 8 and support an optional 5-group rollup (section 3). Confirm which is the primary public-facing count.
- **Yojnas collection vs reuse Posts:** This PRD specifies a dedicated `yojnas` collection (scheme-specific fields) while keeping `posts` for news. Confirm.
- **Bilingual scope:** Hindi + English (full localization) vs English-first with Hindi later.
- **Category spanning:** can a single yojna belong to multiple categories (`hasMany`) or exactly one?
